{"title_page": "Param Singh (actor)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2016}}\n{{Use indian english|date=December 2016}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Param Singh Bhatia \n| image              =\n| image_size         = 50 KB\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1988|9|8|df=yes}}\n| birth_place        = [[Mumbai]], [[Maharashtra]], [[India]]\n| alma_mater         = Billimoria High School<br />[[Smt. M.M.K College of Commerce & Economics|Smt. M.M.K College]]\nUniversity - Regent University London \n| occupation         = Actor\n| years_active       = 2013-present\n| awards             = \n| signature          = \n| nationality        = [[India|Indian]]\n| denomination       = \n| website            = \n}}\n'''Param Singh''' (born on 8 September 1988) is an Indian television actor.\n\n==Career==\nParam is a trained actor from Barry John Acting Studio. After completing his training he did a few stage shows and advertisements ( Hero Bikes, Dulux, Monaco Biscuit, Ferero Rocher). Originally from a Chauhan family, he started his career with ''[[Sadda Haq]]'' in 2013 where he played the role of Randhir Singh Shekhawat, opposite [[Harshita Gaur]] in [[Channel V India]]'s '' [[Sadda Haq (TV series)|Sadda Haq]]'', (Season 1 & 2) produced by [[Inspire Films]]. The show had a great run and it ended in 2016.\n\nIn 2017 he did a show for [[Life OK]] named ''[[Ghulaam]]'' where he essayed the lead character Rangeela, opposite [[Niti Taylor]] and [[Vikas Manaktala]].\n\nLater, Singh played Dhruv Narang for Beyond Originals' web series called \"Black Coffee\", created by [[Yash A Patnaik]] and Mamta Patnaik, with his [[Sadda Haq (TV series)|Sadda Haq]] co-star Harshita Gaur.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/1150806/jsp/t2/story_35542.jsp | title= Param is your pick | website= telegraphindia.com |date= Aug 6, 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.tellychakkar.com/tv/features/10-unknown-interesting-facts-about-param-singh-084 | title= 10 unknown interesting facts about Param Singh | website= tellychakkar.com |date= Apr 27, 2014 }}</ref>\n\nHe was also 'The Highest Placed Newcomer\u2019 in Eastern Eye's 50 Sexiest Asian Men's List in 2016 .<ref>https://twitter.com/SanDhirParShFC/status/941264660019286016/photo/1</ref><ref>https://twitter.com/sandhirians/status/809019719030337536/photo/1</ref>\n\nIn 2018 he played Fawad Ashraf in [[Star Plus]]'s show ''[[Mariam Khan - Reporting Live]]'' but the show ended in early 2019 due to low TRPs. In August 2019 he signed [[Balaji Telefilms]] show ''[[Haiwaan : The Monster]]'' which aired on [[Zee TV]] opposite [[Ridhima Pandit]]. He portrayed Randhir Agnihotri a young, fun loving but smart scientist. The show ended on 16 February 2020.\n\n==Television==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! Year !! Series !! Role !! Network !! Reference\n|-\n| 2013 || ''[[Parvarrish]]''|| Yudhishthir Sharma (Yudi)|| [[Sony TV]] ||\n|-\n| 2013\u20132016 || ''[[Sadda Haq (TV series)|Sadda Haq: My Life, My Choice]]'' || Randhir Singh Shekhawat || [[Channel V]] || \n|-\n| 2017 || ''[[Ghulaam]]'' || Rangeela || [[Life OK]] || <ref>{{cite web|url = http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/life-ok-is-all-set-to-unveil-its-next-big-show-ghulaam/articleshow/56383952.cms|title = Life OK is all set to unveil its next big show 'Ghulaam|publisher = [[The Times of India]]|date = 7 January 2017|accessdate = 8 January 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2018\u20132019 || ''[[Mariam Khan - Reporting Live|Mariam Khan: Reporting Live]]'' || Fawad Ashraf || [[Star Plus]] || \n|-\n| 2019\u20132020 || ''[[Haiwaan : The Monster|Haiwaan]]'' || Randhir Agnihotri || [[Zee TV]] || <ref>{{cite web|url =https://www.pinkvilla.com/tv/news-gossip/ekta-kapoors-upcoming-sci-fi-thriller-haivan-star-param-singh-and-ridhima-pandit-456764|title =\"Ekta Kapoor's upcoming sci fi thriller Haivan to star Param Singh and Ridhima Pandit?\"}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Web series==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Shows\n! Role\n! Channel\n! Co-actor\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''Black Coffee''\n| Dhruv Narang (Lead Role)\n| Beyond Originals ([[YouTube]])\n| [[Harshita Gaur]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2019\n| ''Holycross''\n| Akash (Lead Role)\n| [[Sony Liv]]\n| [[Auritra Ghosh]]\n|-\n| ''Tadap''\n| Mohit (Lead Role)\n| [[Ullu App]]\n| [[Shiny Dixit]]\n|}\n\n==Short film==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Films\n! Role\n! Channel\n! Co-actor\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''Aman''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=G8fZe-dI-eQ|title=Aman Full Short Film|last=Mad Over Fun|via=YouTube}}</ref>\n| Aman (Lead Role)\n| Mad Over Fun ([[YouTube]])\n| [[Harshita Gaur]]\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|50em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|nm7477061}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Singh, Param}}\n[[Category:1988 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Uttar Pradesh]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2016}}\n{{Use indian english|date=December 2016}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Param Singh Bhatia \n| image              =\n| image_size         = 50 KB\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1988|9|8|df=yes}}\n| birth_place        = [[Mumbai]], [[Maharashtra]], [[India]]\n| alma_mater         = Billimoria High School<br />[[Smt. M.M.K College of Commerce & Economics|Smt. M.M.K College]]\n| occupation         = Actor\n| years_active       = 2013-present\n| awards             = \n| signature          = \n| nationality        = [[India|Indian]]\n| denomination       = \n| website            = \n}}\n'''Param Singh''' (born on 8 September 1988) is an Indian television actor.\n\n==Career==\nParam is a trained actor from Barry John Acting Studio. After completing his training he did a few stage shows and advertisements ( Hero Bikes, Dulux, Monaco Biscuit, Ferero Rocher). Originally from a Chauhan family, he started his career with ''[[Sadda Haq]]'' in 2013 where he played the role of Randhir Singh Shekhawat, opposite [[Harshita Gaur]] in [[Channel V India]]'s '' [[Sadda Haq (TV series)|Sadda Haq]]'', (Season 1 & 2) produced by [[Inspire Films]]. The show had a great run and it ended in 2016.\n\nIn 2017 he did a show for [[Life OK]] named ''[[Ghulaam]]'' where he essayed the lead character Rangeela, opposite [[Niti Taylor]] and [[Vikas Manaktala]].\n\nLater, Singh played Dhruv Narang for Beyond Originals' web series called \"Black Coffee\", created by [[Yash A Patnaik]] and Mamta Patnaik, with his [[Sadda Haq (TV series)|Sadda Haq]] co-star Harshita Gaur.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/1150806/jsp/t2/story_35542.jsp | title= Param is your pick | website= telegraphindia.com |date= Aug 6, 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.tellychakkar.com/tv/features/10-unknown-interesting-facts-about-param-singh-084 | title= 10 unknown interesting facts about Param Singh | website= tellychakkar.com |date= Apr 27, 2014 }}</ref>\n\nHe was also 'The Highest Placed Newcomer\u2019 in Eastern Eye's 50 Sexiest Asian Men's List in 2016 .<ref>https://twitter.com/SanDhirParShFC/status/941264660019286016/photo/1</ref><ref>https://twitter.com/sandhirians/status/809019719030337536/photo/1</ref>\n\nIn 2018 he played Fawad Ashraf in [[Star Plus]]'s show ''[[Mariam Khan - Reporting Live]]'' but the show ended in early 2019 due to low TRPs. In August 2019 he signed [[Balaji Telefilms]] show ''[[Haiwaan : The Monster]]'' which aired on [[Zee TV]] opposite [[Ridhima Pandit]]. He portrayed Randhir Agnihotri a young, fun loving but smart scientist. The show ended on 16 February 2020.\n\n==Television==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! Year !! Series !! Role !! Network !! Reference\n|-\n| 2013 || ''[[Parvarrish]]''|| Yudhishthir Sharma (Yudi)|| [[Sony TV]] ||\n|-\n| 2013\u20132016 || ''[[Sadda Haq (TV series)|Sadda Haq: My Life, My Choice]]'' || Randhir Singh Shekhawat || [[Channel V]] || \n|-\n| 2017 || ''[[Ghulaam]]'' || Rangeela || [[Life OK]] || <ref>{{cite web|url 